abstract: “If there is anything we can negotiate and discuss, and if I can bring something back home, I am ready to go straight away,” President Volodymyr Zelensky said.
snippet: “If there is anything we can negotiate and discuss, and if I can bring something back home, I am ready to go straight away,” President Volodymyr Zelensky said.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said Friday that the Trump administration was committed to supporting Ukraine in its defense against aggression by Russia, though he did not offer President Volodymyr Zelensky the one thing he has sought since last May: an invitation to meet President Trump at the White House.

abstract: The fast-moving coronavirus stemming from China could force companies to re-evaluate their supply chains, potentially returning some jobs to the United States, U.S. Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross said on Thursday.
snippet: The fast-moving coronavirus stemming from China could force companies to re-evaluate their supply chains, potentially returning some jobs to the United States, U.S. Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The fast-moving coronavirus stemming from China could force companies to re-evaluate their supply chains, potentially returning some jobs to the United States, U.S. Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross said on Thursday.
headline_main: China's Coronavirus May Help Boost U.S. Jobs: Ross
headline_print_headline: China's Coronavirus May Help Boost U.S. Jobs: Ross

abstract: The session on Friday could be definitive, most likely capped by a vote on whether to hear new witnesses and consider new evidence.
snippet: The session on Friday could be definitive, most likely capped by a vote on whether to hear new witnesses and consider new evidence.
lead_paragraph: Friday’s session could be definitive, likely capped by a vote on whether to consider new witnesses and evidence. But after that vote, which Republicans are confident will be rejected, things in President Trump’s impeachment trial could become a little messy. Nicholas Fandos, a congressional correspondent for The New York Times, walked me through what to expect.
headline_main: Expect today to be a maze of activity.

abstract: President Kais Saied of Tunisia, an ally of the United States, said on Thursday that the new U.S. plan for peace between Israel and the Palestinians is the "injustice of the century".
snippet: President Kais Saied of Tunisia, an ally of the United States, said on Thursday that the new U.S. plan for peace between Israel and the Palestinians is the "injustice of the century".
lead_paragraph: TUNIS — President Kais Saied of Tunisia, an ally of the United States, said on Thursday that the new U.S. plan for peace between Israel and the Palestinians is the "injustice of the century".
headline_main: Trump's Mideast Plan Is 'Injustice of the Century', U.S.-Allied Tunisian President Says

abstract: John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
snippet: John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
headline_main: Delaney, Longest-Running Democratic Candidate, Ends 2020 Bid
headline_print_headline: Delaney, Longest-Running Democratic Candidate, Ends 2020 Bid

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday sought to defuse tension over Britain's decision to allow China's Huawei a role in its communication network, but described the Chinese Communist Party as the biggest threat of the current era.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday sought to defuse tension over Britain's decision to allow China's Huawei a role in its communication network, but described the Chinese Communist Party as the biggest threat of the current era.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday sought to defuse tension over Britain's decision to allow China's Huawei a role in its communication network, but described the Chinese Communist Party as the biggest threat of the current era.
headline_main: Pompeo Plays Down Rift With Britain Over Huawei, but Steadfast on Chinese Threat
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Plays Down Rift With Britain Over Huawei, but Steadfast on Chinese Threat

abstract: Until late Thursday, he was the lone Republican vocally pushing for witnesses to be called in the impeachment trial.
snippet: Until late Thursday, he was the lone Republican vocally pushing for witnesses to be called in the impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, is the rare Senate Republican — actually the lone Senate Republican until late Thursday —  vocally pushing for witnesses to be called in President Trump’s impeachment trial. He is also the only Senate Republican who is seen as a possible vote to convict the president, an added distinction since Mr. Trump got every House Republican to fall in line.

abstract: Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
snippet: Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
headline_main: Key Senator Alexander Says He Will Not Vote for Impeachment Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Key Senator Alexander Says He Will Not Vote for Impeachment Witnesses

abstract: U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favor of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favor of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favor of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Republican Senator Suggests She May Vote for More Impeachment Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Republican Senator Suggests She May Vote for More Impeachment Witnesses

abstract: Record-low U.S. unemployment, booming equity markets, and continued economic growth may have given President Donald Trump a head start toward reelection, but new analysis of past voting and economic trends in key states suggests the margin is "razor thin" and could be upended by strong turnout among Democrats.
snippet: Record-low U.S. unemployment, booming equity markets, and continued economic growth may have given President Donald Trump a head start toward reelection, but new analysis of past voting and economic trends in key states suggests the margin is "raz...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Record-low U.S. unemployment, booming equity markets, and continued economic growth may have given President Donald Trump a head start toward reelection, but new analysis of past voting and economic trends in key states suggests the margin is "razor thin" and could be upended by strong turnout among Democrats.
headline_main: Good Economy May Mask Trump Vulnerability in Key States: Study
headline_print_headline: Good Economy May Mask Trump Vulnerability in Key States: Study
